text: Newry (pronounced /njɚɹi/; ) is a city in Northern Ireland in the United Kingdom. It is partly in County Armagh and partly in County Down. It is the eighth largest city in Ireland. 27,430 people live in the city. A picture of a local bridge is on some British pound coins. == References == Category:Cities in Northern Ireland Category:County Armagh Category:County Down
